    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.H/3</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Director General of the Pan American Union</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rowe</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-10">January 10,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to send you herewith a
                    copy of the Report of the Subcommittee on Program of the Eighth International
                    Conference of American States, approved at the session of the Governing Board
                    held on January 8th.<note n="1" xml:id="d1fn1">Eighth International Conference
                        of American States, Lima, Peru, <hi rend="italic">Report of the Subcommittee
                            on Program with a list of topics for possible inclusion in the Agenda,
                            Approved by the Governing Board of the Pan American Union at the Session
                            of January 8, 1986</hi> (Washington, Pan American Union [1936]).</note>
                    Attached to the report is a list of topics which may be considered for possible
                    inclusion in the program of the Eighth Conference.</p>
                <p>As you will observe, the report requests that the Governments send to the Pan
                    American Union an expression of their opinion on the program prior to June
                    first.</p>
                <p>I beg to remain [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>L. S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Rowe</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
